    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for this house i'm buying in toronto. i'm kinda confused. whats escrow actually and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In the context of buying a house, escrow refers to a separate account held by your lender that you must fund to cover specific expenses related to the property. An escrow account is typically required for property taxes and insurance, as it helps ensure timely payment of these fees. In Toronto, you likely need an escrow account to cover your share of property taxes and condo fees, which are usually paid quarterly or annually. By setting up an escrow account, your lender can collect these funds when they become due, and then apply them to the property's expenses when your payment is due.",
