    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok that makes sense. so it's basically just a way for the bank to make sure the bills get paid so i dont end up with a lien or something. is there anything else that usually goes into that account? like is it just taxes and insurance or is there more stuff involve in the closing part specifically?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow accounts typically cover a range of expenses, not just taxes and insurance. Other common items that may be paid from the escrow account include condo fees, municipal building charges, and utility deposits. In some cases, the account might also cover other closing costs, like grant funds or reserve fund assessments. Your lender will review the property's specific requirements to ensure you're accounting for all necessary fees.",
      "source": "target",
